        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 3:38PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 24
miles northeast of East Helena, or 28 miles northeast of Helena,
moving east northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Logan On The Smith River.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
